THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 407A of NRS is hereby amended by
2 adding thereto the provisions set forth as sections 2 and 3 of this act.
3 Sec. 2. 1. The Transit-to-Trails Task Force is hereby
4 created.
5 2. The Task Force consists of the following members
6 appointed by the Legislative Commission:
7 (a) One member who represents the Office of the Governor;
8 (b) One member who represents a law enforcement agency in
9 this State;
10 (c) One member who represents a regional transportation
11 commission in a county whose population is 100,000 or more but
12 less than 700,000;
13 (d) One member who represents a regional transportation
14 commission in a county whose population is 700,000 or more;
15 (e) One member who represents a county whose population is
16 less than 100,000;
17 (f) One member who represents the Division;
18 (g) Two members who represent the public and who have an
19 interest in outdoor recreation and transportation;
20 (h) One member who represents an advocacy group relating to
21 transportation and outdoor recreation;
22 (i) One member who represents the United States Bureau of
23 Land Management;
24 (j) One member who represents the United States Forest
25 Service; and
26 (k) One member who represents the United States National
27 Park Service.
28 3. The members of the Task Force shall serve a term of 4
29 years. A member may be reappointed to the Task Force and any
30 vacancy must be filled in the same manner as the original
31 appointment.
32 4. The members of the Task Force serve without
33 compensation and are not entitled to the per diem or travel
34 expenses provided to state officers generally.
35 5. The Task Force shall meet on a quarterly basis. At the first
36 meeting of the Task Force, the members of the Task Force shall
37 elect a Chair and Vice Chair from among its members.
38 6. A majority of the members of the Task Force constitutes a
39 quorum for the transaction of business, and a majority of those
40 members present at any meeting is sufficient for any official
41 action taken by the Task Force.
