1 Sec. 3. The Transit-to-Trails Task Force created by section 2
2 of this act shall:
3 1. Identify high-priority areas for a program to provide or
4 expand access to trails in this State, using public transit, based on
5 the need for transportation infrastructure to improve access to
6 outdoor recreation for communities with limited transportation or
7 parking, with public safety concerns or where the weather of the
8 community makes public transportation a better option for trail
9 access; and
10 2. Identify and apply for grants of money from the Federal
11 Government and private entities for the expansion of public transit
12 that runs to trailheads in this State, including, without limitation,
13 in the high-priority areas identified pursuant to subsection 1.
14 Sec. 4. NRS 407A.500 is hereby amended to read as follows:
15 407A.500 As used in NRS 407A.500 to 407A.620, inclusive,
16 and sections 2 and 3 of this act, unless the context otherwise
17 requires, the words and terms defined in NRS 407A.510, 407A.515
18 and 407A.525 have the meanings ascribed to them in those sections.
19 Sec. 5. The Transit-to-Trails Task Force created by section 2
20 of this act shall prepare and submit a written report to the Director
21 of the Legislative Counsel Bureau for transmittal to the Joint Interim
22 Standing Committee on Growth and Infrastructure describing the
23 activities, findings and conclusions of the Task Force and any
24 recommendations for legislation not later than August 31 of each
25 even-numbered year.
26 Sec. 6. The provisions of NRS 218D.380 do not apply to any
27 provision of this act which adds or revises a requirement to submit a
28 report to the Legislature.
29 Sec. 7. This act becomes effective on July 1, 2025, and expires
30 by limitation on October 1, 2030.
